<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="578" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1842,2011]" pageId="9" pageNumber="578">
As indicated by the key to genera, the five described species listed in this genus, all from the Mexican and Caribbean area, also an undescribed species from 
<collectingCountry box="[900,971,1878,1903]" name="Brazil" pageId="9" pageNumber="578">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, are similar in structure to those placed in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,285,1914,1939]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Leucothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,285,1914,1939]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="578">Leucothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The generic classification of Neotropical dendrothripines remains unclear. Two species described from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[327,395,1950,1975]" name="Brazil" pageId="9" pageNumber="578">Brazil</collectingCountry>
are listed in 
<taxonomicName box="[562,788,1950,1975]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Pseudodendrothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[562,788,1950,1975]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="578">Pseudodendrothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but they are more closely related to 
<taxonomicName box="[1249,1383,1950,1975]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Leucothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1249,1383,1950,1975]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="578">Leucothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[151,292,1986,2011]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Halmathrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,292,1986,2011]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="578">Halmathrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
